 FUN City Theatre has partnered with Chitungwiza Arts Centre to launch a monthly poetry slam in the town.
The poetry platform will be launched on September 5 at Chitungwiza Arts Centre. There are no public arts facilities in Chitungwiza. Marerwa said the event is open to all. “Poets from the town and those from outside are therefore invited to attend the inaugural gathering of the poets of Chitungwiza Poetry Slam to be held from 10 am to 12 noon. “We are happy that finally we now have a home of our own. Come and let us showcase our talents to the world. Some of the poets who confirmed their attendance include renowned academic, author and poet Ignatius Mabasa, Felix Mutasa and Poyetik Eneji, who all hail from the town,” he said.